        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 16 at 9:40PM CDT by NWS Lincoln IL</headline>
        <description>At 939 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Rankin, or 8 miles west of Hoopeston, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hoopeston, Rossville, Potomac, and Rankin.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
